President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Rick Christman for the position of Member, Board of Directors of the Corporation for National and Community Service. Christman has been the CEO of Employment Solutions since 1989 and was previously a Member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for National and Community Service from April 2012 to October 2013. He has a background in working with organizations that support individuals with disabilities, including serving as Executive Director at the Bluegrass Association for Retarded Children and Director for Mental Retardation Services at the Western Kentucky Regional MH-MR Board. Christman holds a B.S. from the University of Wisconsin-Eau Claire and an M.S. from the University of Wisconsin-Stout.